  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    The purpose of this&amp;nbsp;activity&amp;nbsp;is to:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Explore what portions of the business processes can and should be automated.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Understand how software systems that are to be acquired, developed, or deployed will fit into the&#xD;
        organization.&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Derive software requirements for software systems to be acquired, developed, or deployed.&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    [&lt;a class=&quot;elementlinkwithusertext&quot; href=&quot;./../../core.base_rup/customcategories/references_56F06DFD.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;7.755968586980351E-308&quot;>JAC94&lt;/a>] describes three categories of process automation:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Support for improving lead times of business use cases.&amp;nbsp;This category improves the efficiency of the existing&#xD;
        way of working but does not change that way of working.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Support for reorganizing or sequencing the activities of a business process. This category improves business use&#xD;
        cases innovatively and often results in changes to the existing way of working.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Support for monitoring, controlling, and improving the way of working.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    This starts with a reconsideration of the objectives defined for the business-modeling effort. Based on the insight and&#xD;
    experience that the business-modeling team has gained, objectives and expectations might need to be adjusted. Once the&#xD;
    possibilities and constraints for automating and improving the business are agreed upon, the threat of unrealistic&#xD;
    expectations or an over ambitious project is reduced.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The &lt;a class=&quot;elementlinkwithusertext&quot; href=&quot;./../../extend.bus_model/workproducts/rup_business_use_case_14F1BAF2.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;{587A849E-B5F2-4B17-8C7F-1C59B0F5612D}&quot;>Business Use Cases&lt;/a> are analyzed to determine which offer the greatest&#xD;
    potential improvement at the least cost. This is a tradeoff between smaller short-term benefits for relatively less&#xD;
    effort and potentially huge long-term benefits at a greater cost. After the business use cases that would benefit the&#xD;
    most from automation have been determined, the &lt;a class=&quot;elementlinkwithusertext&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../extend.bus_model/workproducts/rup_business_use_case_realization_55CAF00D.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;{47F095EB-E651-4A34-B75B-BACE38ED90C7}&quot;>Business Use-Case Realizations&lt;/a> are analyzed. Software system&#xD;
    requirements are derived from these realizations, providing input for an initial &lt;a class=&quot;elementlinkwithusertext&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../core.base_rup/workproducts/rup_usecase_model_EF15E534.html&quot; guid=&quot;{9C66F2EC-EDEB-4369-9AFB-04B9E7CBCB8E}&quot;>System&#xD;
    Use Case Model&lt;/a>, &lt;a class=&quot;elementlink&quot; href=&quot;./../../core.base_rup/workproducts/rup_analysis_model_76C3B70C.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;{98EA224C-36F6-46E6-AB36-2999382B58B3}&quot;>Analysis Model&lt;/a>, and &lt;a class=&quot;elementlink&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../core.base_rup/workproducts/rup_supplementary_specification_F5ACAA22.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;{B16C2941-791C-44E6-B353-354109B5C9DE}&quot;>Supplementary Specifications&lt;/a>. For more information on this process,&#xD;
    see &lt;a class=&quot;elementlinkwithusertext&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../extend.bus_model/guidances/guidelines/going_from_business_models_to_systems_3B55D8F4.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;1.3212739617274792E-306&quot;>Guideline: Going from Business Model to Systems&lt;/a>.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    It may be necessary to adjust and refine the &lt;a class=&quot;elementlinkwithusertext&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../extend.bus_model/workproducts/rup_business_worker_75AE475B.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;{6C6AD4E6-C7B4-42E1-A3D1-FAC9DC2415B5}&quot;>Business Workers&lt;/a> and &lt;a class=&quot;elementlinkwithusertext&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../extend.bus_model/workproducts/rup_business_use_case_realization_55CAF00D.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;{47F095EB-E651-4A34-B75B-BACE38ED90C7}&quot;>Business Use-Case Realizations&lt;/a> slightly in order to delimit the role&#xD;
    of the software system in the business use-case realizations. For example, responsibilities of human business workers&#xD;
    can be delegated to automated business workers (software systems). These changes must be reviewed to ensure that the &lt;a&#xD;
    class=&quot;elementlink&quot; href=&quot;./../../extend.bus_model/workproducts/rup_business_analysis_model_9449F63A.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;{CF53445C-3351-46C6-810E-8251830029A7}&quot;>Business Analysis Model&lt;/a> remains consistent.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
